h. From a failed nineteenth-century effort to launch a medical specialty called andrology to the contemporary science of paternal effects, there has been a lack of attention to the importance of men's age, health, and exposures. Analyzing historical documents, media messages, and qualitative interviews, GUYnecology demonstrates how this non-knowledge shapes reproductive politics today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aMale reproductive health serviceszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aMale reproductive healthxResearchzUnited StatesxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aage.  abiological clock.  abiomedicine.  abody.  achildhood illness.  achildren.  aclinical care.  agender studies.  ahealthy sperm.  ahistory.  amale.  amedical research.  amiscarriage.  anew fathers.  aoutcomes.  apaternal.  apolitics.  apublic health policy.  areproductive.1 aHealey, Jenna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishz978311070474708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520963986zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520963986423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520963986.jpg  a978-3-11-069041-5  UC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKA